{"data":{"finishReason":"stop","message":"Here are three Monid MCP endpoints that can retrieve Twitter / social‑post data, together with their published per‑call price (all pricing is in US dollars):\n\n| # | Provider / Endpoint | What it does | Per‑call price |\n|---|---------------------|--------------|----------------|\n| 1 | **TikHub** – ` /api/v1/twitter/web/fetch_user_post_tweet` | Returns a specific user’s tweet (the tweet’s content, author info, metrics, etc.) | **$0.0015** |\n| 2 | **BlockRun** – ` /api/v1/surf/search/social/posts` | Full‑text search across social posts (tweets) – you can query for keywords, hashtags, etc., and get matching tweet results | **$0.00825** |\n| 3 | **TikHub** – ` /api/v1/twitter/web/fetch_latest_post_comments` | Retrieves the most recent comments (replies) on a given tweet | **$0.0015** |\n\n**How the list was generated**\n\n1. I first used the Monid tool‑router discovery function (`connection__monid__monid_discover`) with the query *“twitter posts”* to locate relevant live‑data endpoints.  \n2. The discovery response returned a set of candidate endpoints, each including a `price` field indicating the cost per call.  \n3. I selected three distinct endpoints (two from TikHub, one from BlockRun) and extracted their per‑call pricing.\n\nNo endpoint was executed – only the free discovery step was performed, as requested.","sequence":0,"stepIndex":2,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"message.completed","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T11:41:01.052Z"}}
